{
  "doc_id": "53524",
  "text": "Antioxidative and antisenescent activities of an aqueous extract of Acanthopanax koreanum were augmented by fermentation with lactic acid bacteria, Lactobacillus plantarum and Bifidobactrium bifidum [CITATION_1] . Antioxidative activities of soybean products, such as miso, tempeh and natto, fermented with Aspergillus oryzae, Rhizopus oligosporum and Bacillus natto are significantly higher than those of non-fermented steamed soybean [CITATION_2] . Antioxidative and skin whitening activities of soybean extract fermented with Bacillus subtilis are also higher than those of non-fermented soybean extract [CITATION_3] . Fermentation of cultured wild ginseng root and red ginseng extracts with probiotic Bifidobacterium longum strengthens their antioxidative and anti-inflammatory activities [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . These findings imply that probiotic fermentation can offer various advantages in the application of natural products, including the development of functional cosmetic resources.",
